data.title: Prince Francesco, Count of Trapani
data.text:
Prince Francesco of the Two Sicilies, Count of Trapani (Francesco di Paola Luigi Emanuele; 3 August 1827 – 24 September 1892) was born a Prince of the Kingdom of the Two Sicilies and awarded the title Count of Trapani.

Marriage[edit]

On 10 April 1850, Prince Francesco married his niece, Maria Isabella of Austria, Princess of Tuscany, daughter of Leopold II, Grand Duke of Tuscany and his wife Princess Maria Antonia of the Two Sicilies in Florence.

Children[edit]

Princess Maria Antonietta of the Two Sicilies (16 March 1851 – 12 September 1938) married Prince Alfonso of the Two Sicilies, Coont o Caserta and had children.

Prince Leopoldo o the Two Sicilies (24 September 1853 – 4 September 1870)

Princess Maria Teresa Pia of the Two Sicilies (7 January 1855 – 1 September 1856)

Princess Maria Carolina of the Two Sicilies (21 February 1856 – 7 April 1941) married Count Andrzej Przemysław Zamoyski and had children.

Prince Ferdinando of the Two Sicilies (25 May 1857 – 22 July 1859) died young.

Princess Maria Annunziata of the Two Sicilies (21 September 1858 – 20 March 1873) died young.
